1. Introduction

Welcome to MovieNight. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use the MovieNight application.

By using MovieNight, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

2. Information We Collect
a. Information You Provide

MovieNight may collect the following information when you use the app:

Nickname or display name

Room or session information

Messages sent in chat (if chat features exist)

This information is used only to enable the functionality of the application.

b. Automatically Collected Information
When you use the app, certain technical information may be collected automatically, such as:

IP address

Browser type

Device information

Usage data (such as pages visited or actions performed)

This information helps improve performance and troubleshoot issues.

3. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information to:

Provide and maintain the MovieNight service

Enable synchronized video playback with friends

Allow communication between users in rooms

Improve application functionality and performance

Monitor usage to prevent abuse or misuse

4. Cookies and Local Storage

MovieNight may use cookies or browser storage to:

Maintain session information

Remember preferences

Improve user experience

You can disable cookies in your browser settings, though some features may not function properly.

5. Data Sharing

MovieNight does not sell, rent, or trade your personal information.

Information may only be shared:

If required by law

To protect the security and integrity of the application

With service providers required to run the application (such as hosting providers)

6. Data Retention

We retain information only for as long as necessary to operate and maintain the service.

Chat messages, session data, or logs may be automatically deleted after a certain period.

7. Security

We take reasonable steps to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. However, no method of transmission over the Internet is completely secure.

8. Children's Privacy

MovieNight is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

9. Third-Party Services

MovieNight may use third-party services such as:

Video platforms (e.g., YouTube)

Hosting providers

Analytics services

These services have their own privacy policies.

10. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted in this document with an updated date.

